<item>
            <title>[AMQ-3513] initialReconnectDelay is ignored for Failover transport</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-3513</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;initalReconnectDelay is ignored during failover.  If multiple brokers are running, the failover transport attempts to failover immediately and does not honor the initialReconnect delay.  Patch is attached.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
