                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13116022" author="tabish121" created="Wed, 28 Sep 2011 00:05:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Pretty sure bad things will happen if the initalReconnectDelay is set to zero using this patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13116027" author="jgenender" created="Wed, 28 Sep 2011 00:20:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ah right... 0 == forever... ok... fixed it with a guard.  All works now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13116028" author="jgenender" created="Wed, 28 Sep 2011 00:22:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-3513&quot; title=&quot;initialReconnectDelay is ignored for Failover transport&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;AMQ-3513&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;AMQ-3513&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;-take2.patch is attached with the guard.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13116441" author="jgenender" created="Wed, 28 Sep 2011 13:18:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch take 3... I moved the delay above the while loop, so it really is just an initial reconnect and not on every connection.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13116853" author="tabish121" created="Wed, 28 Sep 2011 22:10:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch applied in trunk.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
